Product Photographers FAQs

  • What types of product photography can I get?

    You can get many types of product photos in a few different settings: Outdoor Lifestyle, White background, Indoor Lifestyle and 360.

  • How does the seller get my product?

    Most sellers prefer that you ship your product to the address they provide after you purchase from them. If you have a 100% discount coupon code, that can be an option, too.

  • My product need some preparation, can the seller help with that?

    In most cases, our sellers will offer some basic product preparation. If it’s a complex product or if you have very specific instructions, we recommend reaching out to the seller before ordering.

  • Can my product be shot with a model?

    Of course, many of our sellers offer a “live model” in their Gig, so just filter the marketplace results with it and you’ll find the right options.

  • Will the product be returned to me?

    Since Fiverr doesn’t handle shipping yet, you should check the gig description or contact the seller and see if they offer product return shipping.

  • Do sellers provide retouching and photoshop editing?

    Most sellers do basic photo enhancement. However, we recommend setting expectations prior to placing an order. Keep in mind that retouching will only be applied to the number of photos that you ordered, and not on all photos that were shot.

Why we use cookies

We use cookies and similar technologies (such as web beacons, pixels, tags and scripts) to provide and improve services, personalize your experience, analyze performance, and for marketing purposes, as further detailed below.

A cookie is a piece of information (text file) stored on your device. When you visit our site, we set our own cookies (called first-party cookies) to store information on your device, such as your language preferences or login information. We also use 3rd-party cookies, which are cookies set by our partners (such as Facebook, Linkedin, Google, etc.).

The duration of a cookie depends on its function. “Session cookies” are only active during your online session, while “persistent cookies” will stay active on your device after closing your browser.

Find more information on our full
Cookie Policy.

Essential cookies

Always Active

Some cookies are essential for our service to function and cannot be switched off in our systems. They are used to enable core functionality, such as authentication, security, connection stability, etc. You can always set your browser to block or alert you about these cookies, but this may affect how the website functions.

Analytics Cookies

Analytics cookies help us know which pages are popular and how visitors move around the site. We use them to count visits, check traffic sources, and measure and improve the website’s performance.

Marketing Cookies

Certain 3rd-party service providers and advertising partners manage our advertising on other websites. Such 3rd parties use cookies through our site to provide you with advertising on other websites based on your interests and preferences.
